 for use with the ecosystem of [`tokio`](https://tokio.rs/) libraries.

defs.name: RetryIf
defs.docs:
Future that drives multiple attempts at an action via a retry strategy. Retries are only attempted if
 the `Error` returned by the future satisfies a given condition.

defs.name: strategy
defs.docs: Assorted retry strategies including fixed interval and exponential back-off.

defs.name: ExponentialBackoff
defs.docs: A retry strategy driven by exponential back-off.

attributes.value: / A retry strategy driven by exponential back-off.
/ The power corresponds to the number of past attempts.

defs.name: from_millis
defs.docs:
Constructs a new exponential back-off strategy,
 given a base duration in milliseconds.

attributes.value: / Constructs a new exponential back-off strategy,
/ given a base duration in milliseconds.
/ The resulting duration is calculated by taking the base to the `n`-th power,
/ where `n` denotes the number of past attempts.

defs.name: factor
defs.docs: A multiplicative factor that will be applied to the retry delay.

attributes.value: / A multiplicative factor that will be applied to the retry delay.
/ For example, using a factor of `1000` will make each delay in units of seconds.

defs.name: max_delay
defs.docs: Apply a maximum delay. No retry delay will be longer than this `Duration`.

attributes.value: / Apply a maximum delay. No retry delay will be longer than this `Duration`.

defs.name: FibonacciBackoff
defs.docs: A retry strategy driven by the fibonacci series.

attributes.value: / A retry strategy driven by the fibonacci series.
/ Each retry uses a delay which is the sum of the two previous delays.
/ Depending on the problem at hand, a fibonacci retry strategy might
/ perform better and lead to better throughput than the `ExponentialBackoff`
/ See ["A Performance Comparison of Different Backoff Algorithms under Different Rebroadcast Probabilities for MANETs."](http://www.comp.leeds.ac.uk/ukpew09/papers/12.pdf)
